sets

Interface NavigableSet<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - element type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<E>, Iterable<E>, Set<E>, SortedSet<E>

    public interface NavigableSet<E>
extends SortedSet<E>
    Extends the definition of sorted set whose iterator ascends the set in ascending order. Adds additional useful behavior and should be used in place of SortedSet.
    Author:
    Jacob Malter
